      "On Shashthi the priest performs Bodhan, awakening Durga in the clay image because the Goddess is otherwise in meditation through the year. Kalparambha establishes the sacred space; bel leaves and mango leaves adorn the pandal. The katha explains that the gods could not defeat Mahishasura alone and therefore invoked the sleeping Shakti. Dhak rolls as the face of the idol is unveiled and the city feels Devi has truly arrived.",
